  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 615501dbe4f3fe94fbf4b564abb10237, type: 3}
  m_Name: ModConfig
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  id: specialFlowers
  title: Special Flowers
  author: _Play_
  description: "[i]Guide on how to get first place in BBT2025:\r\nStep 1:[/i]\r\n[hr][/hr][h2]Module's
    manual can be found on the Repository of Manual Pages: https://ktane.timwi.de/[/h2]\r\n[hr][/hr]Developed
    by _Play_.\r\nSong used: tomatoism - Someone Special\r\n[hr][/hr][h2]On the Subject
    of Mod Settings[/h2]\r\nThis module has two mod settings. Use the \"Mod Settings\"
    app on the [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=801400247]Mod
    Selector[/url], added by the [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=1366808675]Tweaks[/url]
    mod to change them, under the \"Special Flowers Settings\" tab:\r\n[list]\r\n[*]
    Short Solve Sound - Makes the module use a shorter version of its solve sound.\r\n[*]
    Non-Lenient Sequence Generation - The module usually generates flower sequences
    so that in every group, every flower after the first appears more-or-less near
    the previous flower (to avoid situations where the defuser needs to drag their
    cursor from one end of the module to the other in just 0.2 seconds). Enabling
    this setting makes the module instead generate sequences in a completely random
    way.\r\n[/list]"
  version: 1.02
  outputFolder: build
  previewImage: {fileID: 2800000, guid: e688a0d117af81c4aa9447c3d0353588, type: 3}
